******
[1] Zhytomyr
Date: Fri 5 Oct 2018
Source: 112 International [edited]
https://112.international/ukraine-top-news/woman-hospitalized-in-ukraine-with-suspicion-in-anthrax-32894.html


In Zhytomyr region, northern Ukraine, a woman from Bilka village was hospitalized with suspected anthrax, the press service of the State Service of Ukraine for Food Safety and Consumer Protection in Zhytomyr region reported. "On [4 Oct 2018], an urgent message was received on the hospitalization of [a citizen] of Bilka village, Korosten area with the suspicion of anthrax (skin form) to the infectious disease section of Korosten Central Hospital. The date of the disease is [1 Oct 2018], the date of the appeal is [4 Oct 2018]. According to the ill woman, only [her] husband lives with her," the message said.

A medical team has been formed to investigate this case of suspected anthrax. "To establish the diagnosis, the biomaterial of the ill [person, presumably], samples of soil and water were selected during the investigation for the lab research. The investigation continues," the message said.

Earlier we reported that an outbreak of anthrax [had been] observed in a village in Saratsky district, Odessa region, southern Ukraine. According to preliminary data, the source of the disease is a domestic cow that was slaughtered for meat. The 5 people who skinned the cow experienced symptoms and were taken to hospitals; they are under the supervision of doctors. Their condition is not life-threatening.

--
